# Mini App Rules

- Mini App is a UI client, not a business-logic layer.
- All domain data must come from backend API.
- Do not call LLM providers from frontend code.
- Do not embed prompts in frontend code.
- Do not compute session lifecycle in the client.
- Do not use local persistence as source of truth.
- Prefer journal, timeline and structured views over chat-like interpretation loops.
- Backend remains responsible for auth, sessions, analysis and persistence.
